This paper is primarily focused on machine learning and neural networks, which suggests that it would likely fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper specifically addresses the issue of training deep neural networks, which is a common problem in the field of neural networks and would further support the classification of cs.LG. The paper also discusses the use of sparse networks, which could potentially fall under the categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates different topologies for sparse networks in the context of image classification, which could fall under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
